 happened if she''d remained with Jonathan? Not often, but regularly over the years. It was impossible not to have imagined that rejected future, a life of many countries, of vast and enduring adventure, of tiny rooms and rental houses. It was the sense of missed opportunity that returned to her, frightening but real, overwhelmingly real.', 11821, 0), (284794, 'Any human anywhere will blossom in a hundred unexpected talents and capacities simply by being given the opportunity to do so.', 217, 0), (284795, 'As soon as you open your mind to doing things differently, the doors of opportunity practically fly off their hinges.', 30064, 0), (284796, 'The most twisted but perennial of American myths is that everyone has an equal opportunity to succeed. (p. 174)', 4515, 0), (284797, 'NOW is a fact that cannot be dodged.', 4033, 0), (284798, 'Opportunity knocks only once.', 48324, 0), (284799, 'We were the ones on scene when everything went down. We weren''t better. We weren''t worse. We were just the ones standing in the blast radius.', 2105, 0), (284800, 'By focusing on possibilities, you can see more than a potential light at the end of the tunnel. The light doesn''t have to be at the end of the tunnel; it can illuminate an opportunity wherever you are.', 14600, 0);
INSERT INTO quotes (id, content, author_id, views) VALUES (284801, 'For a long time that had seemed to her to be the key to life: Life--real life--was just a solitude waiting to be transfigured. If Phillip was with her, the solitude she needed would be shattered, and along with it whatever wondrous thing might have come her way if she had been alone.', 1400, 0), (284802, 'He never missed an opportunity to miss an opportunity', 48325, 0), (284803, 'The truth is that there is opportunity right now in your present day. Every day offers its own set of golden opportunities.', 16545, 0), (284804, 'We need to ask ourselves if we are passive spectators in life as we watch it simply go by or are we ready to grab the bull by its horns and join in the action.', 16545, 0), (284805, 'Pause and remember: It is through our deepest trials and life hardships that we are given the greatest opportunity to find the person we have been looking for our whole life - our authentic beautiful self.', 27055, 0), (284806, 'Opportunity to help others is the opportunity to help yourself in disguise', 6224, 0), (284807, 'Sure, there are little victories here and there that may seem like lucky breaks, but luck is simply when preparation meets opportunity.', 48326, 0), (284808, 'Don''t let the opportunity pass you by. Act! Do something now. Some chances never come again. Seize the moment. Seize the day! Live to the fullest. Live to YOUR fullest potential.', 6242, 0), (284809, 'You must look through an opportunity and not at it', 6224, 0), (284810, 'Opportunities are visible to those who are looking for them.', 6224, 0), (284811, 'Don''t hang yourself with the slack you''ve been given.', 9546, 0), (284812, 'It is a wretched taste to be gratified with mediocrity when the excellent lies before us.', 48327, 0), (284813, 'Sometimes one needs to stay alone, a bit of loneliness gives you the opportunity to knock on the door to your brain, and it opens with a sudden bright idea. But those who never stay alone don''t even know what''s inside their brains.', 7549, 0), (284814, 'You don''t have to believe in coincidences because they happen every day. The trick is to be able to discern when something is more than coincidence.', 48328, 0), (284815, 'If they lacked the opportunity, the strength of their sprit would have been sapped; if they had lacked ability, the opportunity would have been wasted.', 947, 0), (284816, 'No one remembers how you got a chance, they only remember what you did with it.', 9441, 0), (284817, 'Opportunities are taken or created, never given.', 9447, 0), (284818, 'The period of time between eligibility to vote and the start of adulthood is a window of opportunity that the liberals are willing to exploit to their advantage.', 9447, 0), (284819, 'It’s not about some principled debate as to whether I should focus on what I have, or on what I don’t have. Rather, it’s about being thankful that I have the privilege to enjoy the former, and the opportunity to contemplate the latter.', 4397, 0), (284820, 'Times of stress and difficulty are seasons of opportunity when the seeds of progress are sown.', 48329, 0), (284821, 'When opportunity comes, it’s too late to prepare.', 1721, 0), (284822, 'Often doors of opportunity are opened, but few opt to walk through them.', 6353, 0), (284823, 'Opportunity may come to the patient, but always comes to the persistent.', 6353, 0), (284824, 'Even locked doors can be unlocked in time.', 12140, 0), (284825, 'Nobody gets through life without facing challenges. What''s important is how we handle them. Tough times can be excellent opportunities to grow and become a better person.', 19362, 0), (284826, 'Stay alert at all times, alert to any opportunity for rest.', 18820, 0), (284827, 'Opportunity, after all, is only another word for temptation.', 2738, 0), (284828, 'Some look at your strength and see an opportunity and some look at your weaknesses and see an opportunity .', 6354, 0), (284829, 'Some beautiful opportunities a