y is useless.', 11582, 0), (284994, 'Aubrey Fitzwilliam knew that crisis was another word for opportunity.', 48345, 0), (284995, 'what risk to a common man is an opportunity for a wise', 48346, 0), (284996, 'If opportunity doesn''t knock, build a door and open it, stop waiting around for someone to give it to you', 48347, 0), (284997, 'Allowing yourself to be a conduitfor opportunity requires a brand new outlook on life. Lady fortunecannot enter a locked door, you know. And contrary to that wellknownsaying, she has rarely been known to knock', 23155, 0), (284998, 'I think the reason I choose the comic approach so often is because it''s harder, therefore affording me the opportunity to show off.', 138, 0), (284999, 'I find so many opportunities to fall, to falter, and fail when I refuse to surrender to change. Change will come into my room and rearrange my tidy world. Then like dominoes, one things changed falls upon another until it feels like the world is collapsing around me. But when I yield, when I surrender to the necessary change, I can stand back and look at the beautiful picture created by what seemed to be my world falling apart.', 26454, 0), (285000, 'Life is full of doors that don''t open when you knock, equally spaced amid those that open when don''t want them to.', 1610, 0);
